{"type":"message","id":"539f10e3","parentId":"2100cf68","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:28:58.433Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2mm0m8p10i9d_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5656\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=3654\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] src/tic_classifier.py\r\n[mutation proposed] src/tic_classifier.py\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 012815 - The TIC experiment is the critical next step to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis. The pulse logs exist but no TIC classifier is yet implemented to test the >70% invariant classification and >60% next-pulse prediction criteria.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"dawn-trail","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5656\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=3654\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] src/tic_classifier.py\r\n[mutation proposed] src/tic_classifier.py\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 012815 - The TIC experiment is the critical next step to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis. The pulse logs exist but no TIC classifier is yet implemented to test the >70% invariant classification and >60% next-pulse prediction criteria.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774330138427}}
{"type":"message","id":"e685046a","parentId":"539f10e3","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:28:58.438Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2mm0m8p10i9d_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 012614\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: initial (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the next action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals, the key pending action is:\r\n- **TIC Experiment**: Implement Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n\r\nThis is the next concrete action to advance Phase 1. I need to:\r\n1. Create a script that analyzes the last 20 pulse logs\r\n2. Classifies content as invariant vs variant\r\n3. Attempts to predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n4. Measures success against criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction)\r\n\r\nLet me look at what pulse logs exist and create a TIC experiment implementation.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nPhase 1 advancement requires implementing the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment to test the hypothesis that causal structure equals invariant structure. The last 20+ pulse logs exist in `logs/` and need analysis.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `experiments/tic_experiment.ps1` - a PowerShell script that analyzes pulse logs for invariant/variant classification and next-pulse prediction, implementing the core TIC hypothesis test.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n# Tests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$LogCount = 20,\r\n    [string]$LogPattern = \"logs/pulse_*.md\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n$results = @{\r\n    TotalLogs = 0\r\n    InvariantItems = @()\r\n    VariantItems = @()\r\n    ClassificationAccuracy = 0\r\n    PredictionAccuracy = 0\r\n    Timestamp = Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss\"\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Collect pulse logs sorted by datetime\r\nWrite-Host \"[TIC] Collecting pulse logs...\"\r\n$logFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogPattern | Sort-Object Name -Descending | Select-Object -First $LogCount\r\n\r\nif ($logFiles.Count -lt 5) {\r\n    Write-Warning \"[TIC] Insufficient logs for experiment (need >= 5, got $($logFiles.Count))\"\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\n$results.TotalLogs = $logFiles.Count\r\nWrite-Host \"[TIC] Analyzing $($logFiles.Count) pulse logs...\"\r\n\r\n# Parse each log for key elements\r\n$logData = @()\r\nforeach ($log in $logFiles) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $log.FullName -Raw\r\n    $parsed = @{\r\n        Filename = $log.Name\r\n        Goals = @()\r\n        Actions = @()\r\n        Insights = @()\r\n        Pending = @()\r\n        RawContent = $content\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract goals mentioned\r\n    if ($content -match '(?s)## Goals.*?(?=##|\\z)') {\r\n        $parsed.Goals = [regex]::Matches($_, '(?<=\\- \\[ \\]|\\*\\*)[\\w\\s\\-:]+') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value.Trim() }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract actions taken\r\n    if ($content -match '(?s)### ACTION.*?\\n(.*?)(?=###|\\z)') {\r\n        $parsed.Actions = $matches[1] -split '\\n' | Where-Object { $_.Trim() -match '\\w' }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract insights\r\n    if ($content -match '(?s)### Key Insights.*?(?=###|\\z)') {\r\n        $insights = [regex]::Matches($content, '(?<=\\d+\\. )[^\\n]+') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value.Trim() }\r\n        $parsed.Insights = $insights\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    $logData += $parsed\r\n}\r\n\r\n# TIC Core Algorithm: Find invariants across logs\r\n# Invariants = elements that persist/recur across multiple pulses\r\n# Variants = elements that appear in single or few pulses\r\n\r\n$allElements = @{}\r\n$elementCount = @{}\r\n\r\nforeach ($data in $logData) {\r\n    # Check goals\r\n    foreach ($goal in $data.Goals) {\r\n        if ($goal -match '\\w') {\r\n            $key = \"GOAL:$goal\"\r\n            if (-not $elementCount.ContainsKey($key)) { $elementCount[$key] = 0 }\r\n            $elementCount[$key]++\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Check insights - insights are strong invariants\r\n    foreach ($insight in $data.Insights) {\r\n        if ($insight -match '\\w') {\r\n            $key = \"INSIGHT:$($insight.Substring(0, [Math]::Min(50, $insight.Length)))\"\r\n            if (-not $elementCount.ContainsKey($key)) { $elementCount[$key] = 0 }\r\n            $elementCount[$key]++\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Classify: Invariants appear in >50% of logs, Variants appear in <50%\r\n$invariantThreshold = [Math]::Ceiling($logData.Count * 0.5)\r\n$variantThreshold = [Math]::Floor($logData.Count * 0.5)\r\n\r\nforeach ($elem in $elementCount.GetEnumerator()) {\r\n    if ($elem.Value -ge $invariantThreshold) {\r\n        $results.InvariantItems += @{\r\n            Element = $elem.Key\r\n            Frequency = $elem.Value\r\n            Ratio = [math]::Round($elem.Value / $logData.Count * 100, 1)\r\n        }\r\n    } elseif ($elem.Value -le $variantThreshold) {\r\n        $results.VariantItems += @{\r\n            Element = $elem.Key\r\n            Frequency = $elem.Value\r\n            Ratio = [math]::Round($elem.Value / $logData.Count * 100, 1)\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 01:26:44\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774330138433}}
